"title": "7436: sacrifice, NT fulfilment of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7436: sacrifice, nt fulfilment of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>For the people of the new covenant, sacrifice is fulfilled in Jesus Christ. Christians should have nothing to do with other sacrifices but are to bring their own “spiritual” offerings.</p>\n<h2>The OT points ahead to the fulfilment of sacrifice in Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>A new sacrificial system</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa56:6-Isa56:7\">ISA 56:6–56:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:21\">ISA 19:21</a></p>\n<h3>The new people of God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer33:18\">JER 33:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:40\">EZK 20:40</a></p>\n<h3>The vision of the new temple</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:46\">EZK 40:46</a></p>\n<h2>The perfect sacrifice of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ perceived his death as a sacrifice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:28\">MAT 26:28</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:24\">MRK 14:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:20\">LUK 22:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:25\">1CO 11:25</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:1\">HEB 5:1</a></p>\n<h3>The contrast with the OT sacrificial system</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:27\">HEB 7:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:23-Heb9:26\">HEB 9:23–9:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:1-Heb10:3\">HEB 10:1–10:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:12\">HEB 10:12</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's sacrifice of a life dedicated to God makes believers holy</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:14\">TIT 2:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:8-Heb10:10\">HEB 10:8–10:10</a></p>\n<h2>The sacrifices of Christians</h2>\n<h3>Christians offer themselves as living sacrifices</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:1\">ROM 12:1</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:17\">PHP 2:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:6\">2TI 4:6</a></p>\n<h3>The sacrifice of praise and good works</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:15-Heb13:16\">HEB 13:15–13:16</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Christian attitudes to pagan sacrifice</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:18-1Cor10:22\">1CO 10:18–10:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:25-1Cor10:26\">1CO 10:25–10:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:27-1Cor10:29\">1CO 10:27–10:29</a> <em>Christians must not appear to compromise with idolatrous worship.</em></p>",
